{"line":"{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Windows\\\\\\\\System32\\\\\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\\\\\v1.0\\\\\\\\powershell.exe\\\" -NoProfile -Command 'Get-Content README.md'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}","parsed":{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Windows\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -NoProfile -Command 'Get-Content README.md'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}}
{"line":"{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Windows\\\\\\\\System32\\\\\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\\\\\v1.0\\\\\\\\powershell.exe\\\" -NoProfile -Command 'Get-Content README.md'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# cc-manager\\r\\n\\r\\n`cc-manager` is an interactive terminal app that puts a **controller agent** (Codex CLI) in front of **Claude Code**.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe visible loop is:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. **User** sends a message in the shell.\\r\\n2. **Controller** (Codex) decides whether to:\\r\\n   - reply directly and stop, or\\r\\n   - launch **Claude Code** with the next worker prompt.\\r\\n3. **Claude Code** runs and its output is streamed live in the terminal.\\r\\n4. When Claude finishes, the **Controller** runs again, reviews the result and repository state, and decides the next Claude message or emits **STOP**.\\r\\n5. The shell stays open after **STOP** and waits for the next user instruction.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat makes the controller behave like a developer using Claude Code on behalf of the human manager.\\r\\n\\r\\n## What this implementation guarantees\\r\\n\\r\\n- The shell remains open after `STOP`.\\r\\n- The controller can answer simple messages directly without launching Claude Code.\\r\\n- When the controller delegates, the app prints the exact Claude prompt it is sending.\\r\\n- Claude output is streamed in real time.\\r\\n- After Claude exits, the controller gets another turn and can inspect the repository before deciding the next step.\\r\\n- The same Claude session is reused across worker turns in the same run.\\r\\n- Runs are persisted under `.cc-manager/runs/<run-id>` and can be resumed later.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Install\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm install\\r\\nnpm link\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nNode 18.17+ is required.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Interactive shell\\r\\n\\r\\nStart the shell in the repository you want to manage:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncd /path/to/repo\\r\\ncc-manager\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can also point it at another repo/state directory:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager --repo /path/to/repo --state-dir /path/to/state\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n### Shell behavior\\r\\n\\r\\n- If no run is attached, plain text starts a new run.\\r\\n- If a run is attached, plain text becomes the next user message for that run.\\r\\n- After the controller emits `STOP`, the shell stays attached to the run and waits for the next message.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Shell commands\\r\\n\\r\\n```text\\r\\n/help                Show help\\r\\n/new <message>       Start a brand new run and send the first message\\r\\n/resume <run-id>     Attach to an existing run\\r\\n/use <run-id>        Alias for /resume\\r\\n/run                 Continue an interrupted request in the current run\\r\\n/status              Show status for the attached run\\r\\n/list                List saved runs\\r\\n/logs [n]            Show the last n event lines for the attached run\\r\\n/detach              Detach from the current run\\r\\n/quit                Exit the shell\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## One-shot usage\\r\\n\\r\\nStart a new run, process until `STOP`, then exit:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager run \\\"Please do fixes in this repository until all unit tests pass\\\"\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nResume an existing run with another user message:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager resume <run-id> \\\"Good job. Thank you\\\"\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nShow run status:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager status <run-id>\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nShow recent events:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager logs <run-id> --tail 80\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nList runs:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager list\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nVerify binaries:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\ncc-manager doctor\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Important defaults\\r\\n\\r\\n### Controller (Codex)\\r\\n\\r\\nBy default the controller uses:\\r\\n\\r\\n- `codex exec`\\r\\n- `codex exec resume <session-id>` after the first controller turn\\r\\n- `--json`\\r\\n- `--output-schema`\\r\\n- `--output-last-message`\\r\\n- `--ask-for-approval never`\\r\\n- `--sandbox workspace-write`\\r\\n\\r\\nThe controller prompt explicitly tells Codex to **inspect and verify only** and to avoid editing files itself. Claude Code is the worker that performs actual repository changes.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Worker (Claude Code)\\r\\n\\r\\nBy default the worker uses:\\r\\n\\r\\n- `claude -p`\\r\\n- `--output-format stream-json`\\r\\n- `--verbose`\\r\\n- `--include-partial-messages`\\r\\n- `--session-id <uuid>` for the first worker turn\\r\\n- `--resume <session-id>` on later worker turns\\r\\n- `--allowedTools \\\"Bash,Read,Edit\\\"`\\r\\n- a default appended system prompt that encourages concise progress narration\\r\\n\\r\\n## Useful options\\r\\n\\r\\n```text\\r\\n--repo <path>\\r\\n--state-dir <path>\\r\\n--codex-bin <path>\\r\\n--claude-bin <path>\\r\\n--controller-model <name>\\r\\n--controller-profile <name>\\r\\n--controller-sandbox <read-only|workspace-write|danger-full-access>\\r\\n--controller-config <key=value>            repeatable\\r\\n--controller-skip-git-repo-check\\r\\n--controller-extra-instructions <text>\\r\\n--worker-model <name>\\r\\n--worker-session-id <uuid>\\r\\n--worker-allowed-tools <rules>\\r\\n--worker-tools <rules>\\r\\n--worker-disallowed-tools <rules>\\r\\n--worker-permission-prompt-tool <name>\\r\\n--worker-max-turns <n>\\r\\n--worker-max-budget-usd <amount>\\r\\n--worker-add-dir <path>                    repeatable\\r\\n--worker-append-system-prompt <text>\\r\\n--raw-events\\r\\n--quiet\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Saved run layout\\r\\n\\r\\nEach run is stored under:\\r\\n\\r\\n```text\\r\\n.cc-manager/\\r\\n  runs/\\r\\n    <run-id>/\\r\\n      manifest.json\\r\\n      controller-decision.schema.json\\r\\n      events.jsonl\\r\\n      transcript.jsonl\\r\\n      requests/\\r\\n        req-0001/\\r\\n          loop-0001/\\r\\n            controller.prompt.txt\\r\\n            controller.stdout.log\\r\\n            controller.stderr.log\\r\\n            controller.final.json\\r\\n            worker.prompt.txt\\r\\n            worker.stdout.log\\r\\n            worker.stderr.log\\r\\n            worker.final.json\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n## Tests\\r\\n\\r\\nThis repo includes fake Codex and Claude binaries plus integration tests that verify the exact visible control loop:\\r\\n\\r\\n- greeting -> controller replies directly -> `STOP`\\r\\n- real work -> controller delegates -> Claude streams -> controller reviews -> controller delegates again -> `STOP`\\r\\n- follow-up user message on the same run -> controller replies directly -> `STOP`\\r\\n\\r\\nRun them with:\\r\\n\\r\\n```bash\\r\\nnpm test\\r\\n```\\r\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}","parsed":{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Windows\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -NoProfile -Command 'Get-Content README.md'","aggregated_output":"# cc-manager\r\n\r\n`cc-manager` is an interactive terminal app that puts a **controller agent** (Codex CLI) in front of **Claude Code**.\r\n\r\nThe visible loop is:\r\n\r\n1. **User** sends a message in the shell.\r\n2. **Controller** (Codex) decides whether to:\r\n   - reply directly and stop, or\r\n   - launch **Claude Code** with the next worker prompt.\r\n3. **Claude Code** runs and its output is streamed live in the terminal.\r\n4. When Claude finishes, the **Controller** runs again, reviews the result and repository state, and decides the next Claude message or emits **STOP**.\r\n5. The shell stays open after **STOP** and waits for the next user instruction.\r\n\r\nThat makes the controller behave like a developer using Claude Code on behalf of the human manager.\r\n\r\n## What this implementation guarantees\r\n\r\n- The shell remains open after `STOP`.\r\n- The controller can answer simple messages directly without launching Claude Code.\r\n- When the controller delegates, the app prints the exact Claude prompt it is sending.\r\n- Claude output is streamed in real time.\r\n- After Claude exits, the controller gets another turn and can inspect the repository before deciding the next step.\r\n- The same Claude session is reused across worker turns in the same run.\r\n- Runs are persisted under `.cc-manager/runs/<run-id>` and can be resumed later.\r\n\r\n## Install\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnpm install\r\nnpm link\r\n```\r\n\r\nNode 18.17+ is required.\r\n\r\n## Interactive shell\r\n\r\nStart the shell in the repository you want to manage:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncd /path/to/repo\r\ncc-manager\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can also point it at another repo/state directory:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager --repo /path/to/repo --state-dir /path/to/state\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Shell behavior\r\n\r\n- If no run is attached, plain text starts a new run.\r\n- If a run is attached, plain text becomes the next user message for that run.\r\n- After the controller emits `STOP`, the shell stays attached to the run and waits for the next message.\r\n\r\n### Shell commands\r\n\r\n```text\r\n/help                Show help\r\n/new <message>       Start a brand new run and send the first message\r\n/resume <run-id>     Attach to an existing run\r\n/use <run-id>        Alias for /resume\r\n/run                 Continue an interrupted request in the current run\r\n/status              Show status for the attached run\r\n/list                List saved runs\r\n/logs [n]            Show the last n event lines for the attached run\r\n/detach              Detach from the current run\r\n/quit                Exit the shell\r\n```\r\n\r\n## One-shot usage\r\n\r\nStart a new run, process until `STOP`, then exit:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager run \"Please do fixes in this repository until all unit tests pass\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nResume an existing run with another user message:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager resume <run-id> \"Good job. Thank you\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nShow run status:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager status <run-id>\r\n```\r\n\r\nShow recent events:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager logs <run-id> --tail 80\r\n```\r\n\r\nList runs:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager list\r\n```\r\n\r\nVerify binaries:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncc-manager doctor\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Important defaults\r\n\r\n### Controller (Codex)\r\n\r\nBy default the controller uses:\r\n\r\n- `codex exec`\r\n- `codex exec resume <session-id>` after the first controller turn\r\n- `--json`\r\n- `--output-schema`\r\n- `--output-last-message`\r\n- `--ask-for-approval never`\r\n- `--sandbox workspace-write`\r\n\r\nThe controller prompt explicitly tells Codex to **inspect and verify only** and to avoid editing files itself. Claude Code is the worker that performs actual repository changes.\r\n\r\n### Worker (Claude Code)\r\n\r\nBy default the worker uses:\r\n\r\n- `claude -p`\r\n- `--output-format stream-json`\r\n- `--verbose`\r\n- `--include-partial-messages`\r\n- `--session-id <uuid>` for the first worker turn\r\n- `--resume <session-id>` on later worker turns\r\n- `--allowedTools \"Bash,Read,Edit\"`\r\n- a default appended system prompt that encourages concise progress narration\r\n\r\n## Useful options\r\n\r\n```text\r\n--repo <path>\r\n--state-dir <path>\r\n--codex-bin <path>\r\n--claude-bin <path>\r\n--controller-model <name>\r\n--controller-profile <name>\r\n--controller-sandbox <read-only|workspace-write|danger-full-access>\r\n--controller-config <key=value>            repeatable\r\n--controller-skip-git-repo-check\r\n--controller-extra-instructions <text>\r\n--worker-model <name>\r\n--worker-session-id <uuid>\r\n--worker-allowed-tools <rules>\r\n--worker-tools <rules>\r\n--worker-disallowed-tools <rules>\r\n--worker-permission-prompt-tool <name>\r\n--worker-max-turns <n>\r\n--worker-max-budget-usd <amount>\r\n--worker-add-dir <path>                    repeatable\r\n--worker-append-system-prompt <text>\r\n--raw-events\r\n--quiet\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Saved run layout\r\n\r\nEach run is stored under:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n.cc-manager/\r\n  runs/\r\n    <run-id>/\r\n      manifest.json\r\n      controller-decision.schema.json\r\n      events.jsonl\r\n      transcript.jsonl\r\n      requests/\r\n        req-0001/\r\n          loop-0001/\r\n            controller.prompt.txt\r\n            controller.stdout.log\r\n            controller.stderr.log\r\n            controller.final.json\r\n            worker.prompt.txt\r\n            worker.stdout.log\r\n            worker.stderr.log\r\n            worker.final.json\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\nThis repo includes fake Codex and Claude binaries plus integration tests that verify the exact visible control loop:\r\n\r\n- greeting -> controller replies directly -> `STOP`\r\n- real work -> controller delegates -> Claude streams -> controller reviews -> controller delegates again -> `STOP`\r\n- follow-up user message on the same run -> controller replies directly -> `STOP`\r\n\r\nRun them with:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnpm test\r\n```\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}}
